title: ArcGIS Enterprise patch status
agents: windows
catalog: app
license: GPLv2
distribution: community
description:
 Monitors ArcGIS Enterprise components for available patches by comparing
 installed patch QFE_IDs from the Windows registry against Esri's patch
 notification feed at content.esri.com.

 Discovers all patchable Esri components under HKLM\SOFTWARE\ESRI by
 checking for the QFEPatchFinder or QFEARP markers that Esri places on
 patchable product keys. One service is created per discovered component.

 Components confirmed from real registry exports and marked VERIFIED in
 the plugin source: ArcGIS Server, Portal for ArcGIS, ArcGIS Data Store.
 Other components including GeoEvent Server, Web Adaptor, Notebook Server,
 Mission Server, and Video Server use unverified key patterns and QFE prefix
 assumptions. Community contributions are welcome to verify these.

 The patch feed JSON is cached locally on the monitored host. If the live
 feed is unreachable the cached copy is used and noted in the service
 output. If both the live fetch and cache fail the service goes WARN.

 Security patches (Critical field set to "security" in the Esri feed) cause
 CRIT regardless of threshold configuration. Non-security patches emit WARN
 by default. Patches available for longer than the configured overdue
 threshold emit CRIT regardless of security status. Both thresholds are
 configurable per host and per component via the service monitoring rule.

item:
 Component display name and installed version, for example
 "ArcGIS Server 11.5" or "Portal for ArcGIS 11.5".

inventory:
 One service is created per patchable ArcGIS Enterprise component found
 under HKLM\SOFTWARE\ESRI on the monitored Windows host.